text.__SUMMARY__:
Acacia latipes is a shrub of the genus Acacia(family Leguminosae or Fabaceae ) and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt and Mid West regions of Western Australia.The dense shrub typically grows to a height of 0.3 to 2 metres (1 to 7 ft). It blooms from June to October and produces yellow flowers.
There are two recognised subspecies:

Acacia latipes subsp. latipes
Acacia latipes subsp. licina
